Plot a tdmore object (typical profile of the population and between subject variability).

plot.tdmore.Rd

Plot a tdmore object (typical profile of the population and between subject variability).

# S3 method for tdmore
plot(x, regimen, covariates = NULL, newdata = NULL,
  bsv = TRUE, mc.subjects = 100, .progress = "none", ...)

Arguments

x

the tdmore object
regimen

the regimen to be predicted
covariates

covariates
newdata

a data.frame with at least TIME and any other columns to plot, NULL to plot all columns from the original observed data between time 0 and max(observationTime) or a numeric vector of times
bsv

add between subject variability, enabled by default
mc.subjects

number of subjects in the monte carlo simulation
.progress

either "none" or "text" to see calculation progress of monte carlo simulations
...

ignored

Value

a ggplot object with the the population prediction
